<DIV1 TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000209.tif" N="59">

<PB REF="00000210.tif" N="60">
<HEAD>Recipes.<I>From Harl. MS.</I> 279, <I>ab.</I> 1430-40 A.D. <NOTE PLACE="head"><I>A pretty MS. that ought to be printed.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P><NOTE PLACE="marg"><B>Potage dyuers .lxiij.</B></NOTE><MILESTONE N="15a" UNIT="folio"><B>Harys in cyueye.</B> Take Harys, &amp; Fle hem, &amp; make hem clene, an hacke hem in gobettys, &amp; sethe hem in Watere &amp; Salt a lytylle; &thorn;an take Pepyr, an Safroun, an Brede, y-grounde y-fere, &amp; temper it wyth Ale. &thorn;an take Oynonys &amp; Percely y-mynced smal to-gederys, &amp; sethe hem be hem self, &amp; after|ward take &amp; do &thorn;er-to a porcyon of vynegre, &amp; dresse in. (See also the recipe for "Harus in Cyue" in <I>Liber Cure Cocorum</I>, p. 21, &amp; that for "Conyngus in cyue" p. 20. <I>Chive</I> is a kind of small onion.)</P>
<P><NOTE PLACE="marg"><B>.lxxiii.</B></NOTE> <MILESTONE N="16a" UNIT="folio"><B>Conyngys in cyveye.</B> Take Conyngys, an fle hem &amp; se&thorn;e hem, &amp; make lyke &thorn;ou woldyst make a sewe, saue alle to-choppe hem, &amp; caste Safroun &amp; lyer &thorn;er-to, &amp; Wyne. (See also "Conyngus in cyue" in <I>L. C. C.</I>, p. 20; and "Conynges in Cyue" in <I>Household Ordinances</I>, p. 434.)</P>
<P><NOTE PLACE="marg"><B>xv.</B></NOTE> <MILESTONE N="39b" UNIT="folio"><B>Doucettes.</B> Take Creme a gode cupfulle, &amp; put it on a stray|noure, &thorn;anne take &yogh;olkys of Eyroun, &amp; put &thorn;er-to, &amp; a lytel mylke; &thorn;en strayne it &thorn;row a straynoure in-to a bolle; &thorn;en take Sugre y-now, &amp; put &thorn;er-to, or ellys hony for defaute<MILESTONE N="40a" UNIT="folio"> of Sugre; &thorn;an coloure it with Safroun; &thorn;an take &thorn;in cofyns, &amp; put it in &thorn;e ovynne lere, &amp; lat hem ben hardyd; &thorn;an take a dyssshe y-fastenyd on &thorn;e pelys ende, &amp; pore &thorn;in comade in-to &thorn;e dyssche, &amp; fro &thorn;e dyssche in-to &thorn;e cofyns; &amp; whan &thorn;ey don a-ryse Wel, teke hem out, &amp; serue hem forth.</P>
<P><NOTE PLACE="marg"><B>xxxvij.</B></NOTE> <MILESTONE N="43b" UNIT="folio"><B>Doucettes.</B> Take Porke &amp; hakke it smal, &amp; Eyroun y-mellyd to-gederys, &amp; a lytel Milke, &amp; melle hem to-gederys with Hony &amp; Pepir, &amp; bake hem in a cofyn, &amp; serue forth.</P>
<P><NOTE PLACE="marg"><B>xxxviij.</B></NOTE> <B>Doucettes a-forcyd.</B> Take Almaunde Milke &amp; &yogh;olkys of Eyroun y-mellid to-gederys, Safroun, Salt, &amp; Hony: dry &thorn;in cofyn, &amp; ley &thorn;in Maribonys &thorn;er-on, &amp; <I>serue</I> forth.</P>
